cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with improving spectrum utilization and spatial reuse efficiency in cellular networks using an ad hoc network overlay. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper analyzes the transmission capacities of the overlaid networks under an outage constraint. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper mentions growing Internet services causing unbalance of uplink and downlink traffic. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper considers the deployment of overlaid networks based on frequency and spatial separation to achieve higher network capacities. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention any security or cryptography-related topics.
